def: Pertaining to, or obtained from, certain umbelliferous plants;as, umbellic acid. Umbellic acid. (Chem.) (a) Anisic acid. [Obs.] (b)A yellow powder obtained from umbelliferone.
Of or pertaining to Napoleon I., or his family; resembling, orhaving the qualities of, Napoleon I. Lowell.
Having trunnions the axes of which lie below the bore; -- saidof a cannon.
The quality or state of being greasy, oiliness; unctuousness;grossness.
A summerhouse so situated as to command an extensive prospect.[Colloq.]
The position or office of an administrator.
Held or being before light; -- a word applied to assemblies ofChristians, in ancient times of persecution, held before light in themorning. "Antelucan worship." De Quincey.

[fragrans. -antis, p.pr. of fragrare to emit a smell offragrance: cf. OF. fragrant. Affecting the olfactory nervesagreeably; sweet of smell; odorous; having or emitting an agreeableperfume.Fragrant the fertile earth After soft showers. Milton.
